Sentencas: Indirect hydrogen production routes presented extensive compatibilities for distributed solid oxide fuel cell systems.
Titulo: Hydrogen production via catalytic propane partial oxidation over Ce1-xMxNiO3-λ (M=Al, Ti and Ca) towards solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) applications

Sentencas: Catalyst activity directly determines hydrogen production and profoundly affects the power generation.
Titulo: Hydrogen production via catalytic propane partial oxidation over Ce1-xMxNiO3-λ (M=Al, Ti and Ca) towards solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) applications

Sentencas: In this work, Ce1-xMxNiO3-lambda (M = Al, Ti and Ca) were synthesized for hydrogen production from propane partial oxidation (POx).
Titulo: Hydrogen production via catalytic propane partial oxidation over Ce1-xMxNiO3-λ (M=Al, Ti and Ca) towards solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) applications

Sentencas: From the results, it indicated that the choice of catalyst compositions could directly affect the microstructure during the preparation process.
Titulo: Hydrogen production via catalytic propane partial oxidation over Ce1-xMxNiO3-λ (M=Al, Ti and Ca) towards solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) applications

Sentencas: Also, different Ce1-xMxNiO3-lambda catalysts displayed distinctive carbon tolerance performances due to the different active particle sizes and surface properties of the catalysts.
Titulo: Hydrogen production via catalytic propane partial oxidation over Ce1-xMxNiO3-λ (M=Al, Ti and Ca) towards solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) applications

Sentencas: In general, the synthesized Ce1-xMxNiO3-lambda catalysts showed higher hydrogen production than a commercial nickel cerium catalyst.
Titulo: Hydrogen production via catalytic propane partial oxidation over Ce1-xMxNiO3-λ (M=Al, Ti and Ca) towards solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) applications

Sentencas: From the observation of a SOFC test system powered by injecting the generated H-2 from catalytic propane POx reaction, the obtained power density of CNO-Al displayed an increase of 22.6% compared to the commercial nickel cerium catalyst.
Titulo: Hydrogen production via catalytic propane partial oxidation over Ce1-xMxNiO3-λ (M=Al, Ti and Ca) towards solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) applications

Sentencas: It was quite impressive that the equivalent hydrogen (160 ml/min) produced over CNO-Al and the obtained power density (482.6 mW/cm(2)) of SOFCs were competitive while CNO-Ca presented an excellent stability with a better carbon tolerance performance for the long-term tests.
Titulo: Hydrogen production via catalytic propane partial oxidation over Ce1-xMxNiO3-λ (M=Al, Ti and Ca) towards solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) applications

Sentencas: The achievements of this work might offer a novel point of view for developing low-cost catalyst towards indirect hydrogen production for SOFC.
Titulo: Hydrogen production via catalytic propane partial oxidation over Ce1-xMxNiO3-λ (M=Al, Ti and Ca) towards solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) applications
